<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="47" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,152,487]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,342,422,448]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[946,970,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">bi</emphasis>
(two) and the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1222,1292,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">cornu</emphasis>
(horn), and refers to the two-pronged structure of the male postpedicel.
</paragraph>
